verbose_text: Tse et al. showed that high levels of proinflammatory cytokines interleukin (IL)-2, IL-6, IL-10, macrophage migration inhibitory factor and tumor necrosis factor alpha (TNF-alpha) in a pregnant woman infected with HBV may affect the pregnancy and increase the risk of miscarriage or affect the newborn, with possible reduction of the Apgar score [XREF_BIBR].
evidence: levels of proinflammatory cytokines interleukin (IL)-2, IL-6, IL-10, macrophage migration inhibitory factor
